message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The symptoms and x-ray findings suggest osteosarcoma, which commonly arises from the periosteum of long bones. Osteosarcoma is derived from osteoblasts in the periosteum, which is the outermost layer of the bone. Bone marrow and epiphyseal plate are not involved in the development of osteosarcoma, and neural crest cells give rise to different types of tissue.
